The paper proposes a novel embedding model for knowledge base completion, which involves learning distributed representations for entities, relations, and words in relation mentions. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to natural language processing, machine learning, and databases. Specifically, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are likely categories given the focus on natural language processing and the use of word embeddings. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possibility given the use of distributed representations and the focus on learning. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possibility given the focus on knowledge base completion and the use of embeddings for inference. Finally, cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category given the focus on knowledge repositories and completion.
